TEMPORARY SOURCE-AVAILABLE NOTICE
==================================

This repository is public so that people can read, follow, and evaluate the
project while it is being built. It is NOT open source yet, and no license
to use, copy, modify, merge, publish, distribute, sublicense, run, or
otherwise reuse this code — in whole or in part — is granted at this time.
All rights are reserved by the copyright holder.

Why this restriction exists right now:

  - The project is under active, fast-moving development. Core architecture
    (worldgen pipeline, entity/AI framework, data-bundling format) is still
    shifting week to week; a fork or reuse today would be built on a
    foundation that may not exist in its current form a week from now.
  - Correctness is verified against real vanilla Minecraft server output
    (a bit-exact region-diff methodology, among other test suites) as the
    project goes — that verification work, and the judgment calls behind
    it, are part of what makes this worth citing/crediting properly once
    it's redistributed, and that's easier to do once the dust settles.
  - This avoids fragmented, prematurely-diverged forks while the project
    finds its shape, and keeps one canonical, correctly-attributed source
    of truth during the period where it changes the most.

This is intentionally temporary. Once the project reaches a stable
milestone, it is the intent of the author to release it under a permissive
open-source license (exact license TBD). Until that happens:

  - You may read the code and clone the repository for personal, private
    evaluation.
  - You may NOT redistribute, publish forks, use this code (or code derived
    from it) in another project, or deploy it as a running service, without
    prior written permission from the copyright holder.
  - Contributions via pull request are welcome for discussion, but merging
    a contribution does not grant the contributor any license beyond what
    this notice grants everyone else — talk to the maintainer first.

This project decompiles and studies official Minecraft: Java Edition server
data/behavior as a reference for compatibility (a common, established
practice for cleanroom-style reimplementations), but does not redistribute
Mojang's code or copyrighted assets. See the source comments throughout
the codebase — particularly `vanilla-src/` (gitignored, never committed)
and the `src/main/resources/vanilla/` data bundle — for how that boundary
is maintained. Nothing in this notice grants any rights to Mojang/Microsoft
intellectual property; Minecraft is a trademark of Mojang Studios.

Questions about licensing, collaboration, or future reuse: open an issue
or reach out to the maintainer directly.
